Manchester United Gets $98 Million From Television, Winning English League

-- B y   C h r i s   E l s e r
-- 
2011-05-24T13:33:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-24/manchester-united-gets-98-million-from-television-winning-english-league.html
Manchester United , which won its 19th
English championship this season, earned 60.4 million pounds
($98 million) from taking the title and appearing on television.  Unitedâ€™s total included 13.6 million pounds for finishing
atop the league, and 17.9 million from overseas broadcast
rights, according to a statement released today by the Premier
League. Chelsea, which finished second, earned 57.7 million
pounds. Arsenal, which ended in fourth, got 56.2 million pounds,
slightly more than third-placed  Manchester City , which earned
55.5 million pounds.  Blackpool, which was relegated to the Championship after
finishing 19th, was the lowest earning club, getting 39.1
million pounds. West Ham, which finished last in the league, got
40.2 million pounds, and Birmingham, the other demoted team, got
39.8 million pounds.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
